Text.Value: Right: 'Descend, and know: upon entering the vaults, you forego the protection of city and church law alike.'

EditorData.NodeContext: Clearing throat, drawing herself up and reciting - no matter how you got there, this is the official bit she does in all cases.

Text.Value: Life's unfair. And you still need a vault pass.
Coinmaiden smile on you.
You wouldn't believe how often we get that one in here.
Meadhoney. Counter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bored, directing us towards the clerk to obtain a pass.

Text.Value: Vault pass.
Aye - Glitterbeard brought some giant down just now. He had eyes as dark as winter's crack, and twice as cold.
Account-holders only from here. Vault pass?

EditorData.NodeContext: Utterly bored, staring straight ahead - looking for our pass to enter the vaults

Text.Value: You wouldn't make it past the second door. But... that'd be cold comfort to my corpse, true enough.
This is the wealthiest banking house on the Coast. Gods' ransom sitting under our feet.
You've got steel in you, no mistake. But it's gold that counts around here.
That's a sad story, truly. Tell it to Meadhoney at the counter - and get a vault pass while you're at it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Blunt acknowledgement of the sad story we've just woven - immediately jumps into directing us to towards the counter, utterly unmoved

Text.Value: Glitterbeard's a little preoccupied with his other clients, true enough. Go on, then.
Eh. Wait. Welcome back, my lord.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly perturbed - this guard has seen Minsc pass down into the vaults before, but never come out again. Minsc now going down again - but the guard knows better than to question important customers.

Text.Value: Go, then, you mad bastard. But if Glitterbeard catches you down there, do me the service of dying before you name any names.
Here it is.
You misunderstand me. I'll be going.
Leave.
I don't have a vault pass.
My pass was stolen. Truly. This is all the coin I have left. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
You've had stranger visitors than me today. I won't be noticed, and you can make a tidy profit. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_3_01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
So talk to Meadhoney, and come back with a vault pass.
You can make some gold, or die guarding someone else's. Choose. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
He also had a vault pass.
Feel free to come back. With a vault pass.
Leave.
Which is to say - keep to your own vault, and you'll be fine.
All that gold you guard, and you never get a taste of it yourself? Seems unfair. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Not the first time that's occurred to me, you know. And Glitterbeard's distracted with his other guests...
A better sum than I expected. You're lucky Glitterbeard's busy with other guests below.
So if it's a bribe you're angling at, well... this I have to hear.
I hear another group descended just before me.
When I am Lord and Tyrant over all the Material Planes, you shall be rewarded beyond your wildest dreams.
Minsc is no lord. Unless... Boo, do you have an account down here? Hah, were your cheeks not ample enough?

EditorData.NodeContext: A bank guard is intimidated by Minsc, remembering him as the Stone Lord. Minsc is non-plussed, and assuming 'my lord' refers to Boo.

Text.Value: I don't have a pass. But I do have some gold...

Synopsis: A guard in the lobby stops players from going to the lower levels unless the player has a bank pass
